            <abstract id="ref27" label="Abstract">In 1994 Peter Drucker published the first full-length biography of Max Shachtman, a key figure in the 1960s civil rights, labor and peace movements. 
                <emph render="italic">Max Shachtman and His Left: A Socialist's Odyssey through the American Century</emph> draws on previously untapped archives and interviews to provide a comprehensive study of an important civil rights figure. This collection consists of 8 interviews on 20 cassette tapes conducted by Drucker in 1986-1989.</abstract>
